1
00:00:19,867 --> 00:00:22,600
Hey, Mikoy, Hazel, come in.

2
00:00:22,667 --> 00:00:24,233
Good news.

3
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:27,333
Celeste and Tonito
will get married

4
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:30,000
here in Sorsogon next week.

5
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,400
Really?

6
00:00:32,467 --> 00:00:36,267
Oh my gosh I'm sure it's going
to be grand and fabulous.

7
00:00:36,367 --> 00:00:38,433
Actually, it's just going
to be simple

8
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,833
because it's very private.

9
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,867
Does the instant wedding
you want to happen

10
00:00:41,933 --> 00:00:43,867
really have something to do
with the grand scheme of things?

11
00:00:43,933 --> 00:00:45,633
Or there are other reasons?

12
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:48,367
Maybe Mikoy's girlfriend
has something to do with it.

13
00:00:48,433 --> 00:00:50,900
Are you trying to prove
something?

14
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:52,600
Dear, please.

15
00:00:52,667 --> 00:00:54,500
My point is I'm
here in Sorsogon.

16
00:00:54,567 --> 00:00:55,900
I'm stuck here.

17
00:00:55,967 --> 00:00:58,800
What will I do? Let's not waste
time. I should get married here.

18
00:00:58,867 --> 00:01:00,900
Tonito is handsome.

19
00:01:00,967 --> 00:01:02,967
Just because he's handsome
and rich

20
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:04,333
they look good together
right away?

21
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:05,900
He's every woman's dream.

22
00:01:05,967 --> 00:01:08,100
Who wouldn't like him?

23
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:10,767
Yes, it's possible that
they look good together

24
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:12,200
but it's also possible
they are not.

25
00:01:12,267 --> 00:01:13,933
Why? Who looks good together?

26
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,267
You and Celeste?

27
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:18,167
Just real talk, if you are not
as rich as Tonito

28
00:01:18,233 --> 00:01:19,700
you will just run out of money.

29
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:24,433
People change and maybe before
she's kind

30
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:26,567
but now she's a witch.

31
00:01:26,633 --> 00:01:29,733
Since you and Tonito
get along very well

32
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:33,267
I am sending you both
to Thailand

33
00:01:33,333 --> 00:01:35,567
to talk to our new business
partners.

34
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:36,900
Only the two of us?

35
00:01:36,967 --> 00:01:40,433
And I expect good results
from the trip.

36
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:43,267
Consider it done.

37
00:01:43,367 --> 00:01:44,900
Get some more.

38
00:01:44,967 --> 00:01:46,767
You should eat a lot.

39
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:48,333
Make yourself full.

40
00:01:50,667 --> 00:01:51,900
So, I'm a witch.

41
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:55,167
Oh my God!

42
00:01:55,233 --> 00:01:56,533
Oh my God. Are you okay?

43
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:59,167
- Are you okay?
- Are you okay?

44
00:01:59,233 --> 00:02:01,133
What happened?

45
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,600
I'm okay.

46
00:02:02,667 --> 00:02:03,867
Thank you.

47
00:02:03,933 --> 00:02:06,933
Maybe she kicked the chair
when she was sitting down.

48
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,133
Are you in pain?

49
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:09,633
She said she's okay.

50
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:11,167
Why did you do that?

51
00:02:11,233 --> 00:02:13,867
For her to tell me that Mikoy
and I don't look good together.

52
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,200
Why? Do they look good together?

53
00:02:15,267 --> 00:02:17,200
She's right, isn't she?

54
00:02:17,267 --> 00:02:20,267
You and Mikoy are not a good
match anymore, Celeste.

55
00:02:20,333 --> 00:02:21,700
Look at you now.

56
00:02:21,767 --> 00:02:24,267
Rubbing elbows with the rich
and famous.

57
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:27,133
Living the glitz and glamour
of high society.

58
00:02:27,200 --> 00:02:29,367
You and Tonito are a perfect
match.

59
00:02:29,433 --> 00:02:32,367
What's wrong if it's you
and Aurelia

60
00:02:32,433 --> 00:02:34,433
who will represent the company?

61
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:37,200
After all, she is our
shareholder.

62
00:02:37,267 --> 00:02:41,333
Your personal agenda has nothing
to do with our business.

63
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,267
If what you need to do
for the company

64
00:02:43,333 --> 00:02:48,967
will be an issue with Celeste,
well you better talk to her now.

65
00:02:49,067 --> 00:02:54,467
If Celeste will stop you,
we will have a problem.

66
00:02:54,533 --> 00:02:56,033
Hello, Love. Are you still busy?

67
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,867
I was about to call you.

68
00:02:57,933 --> 00:02:59,933
You sound exhausted.

69
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,033
Do you want us to talk
some other day?

70
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:03,767
Yeah, better.

71
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:07,167
I don't think my brain can
absorb all information.

72
00:03:07,233 --> 00:03:08,933
You should rest.

73
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:09,967
I love you.

74
00:03:10,033 --> 00:03:11,767
I love you more.

75
00:03:33,700 --> 00:03:35,400
Hello?

76
00:03:35,467 --> 00:03:36,600
Hello, Celeste?

77
00:03:36,667 --> 00:03:39,500
Are you sleeping already?

78
00:03:39,567 --> 00:03:42,433
I just want to remind you
of your community service

79
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:43,500
tomorrow.

80
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,800
Where are we going tomorrow?

81
00:03:46,867 --> 00:03:49,367
In Irosin. We'll have a tree
planting activity.

82
00:03:49,433 --> 00:03:51,667
Do you remember that place?

83
00:03:51,733 --> 00:03:53,900
We often go there when we were
teenagers.

84
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,933
That's where the first time
I shouted that I love you

85
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,733
so much.

86
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:05,267
I love you so much, Celeste!

87
00:04:05,333 --> 00:04:07,200
Hey, don't be like that.

88
00:04:07,267 --> 00:04:09,700
I want to be with you forever!

89
00:04:09,767 --> 00:04:11,900
- What's with you?
- I swear to this stream

90
00:04:11,967 --> 00:04:14,867
and trees that we will never
be separated!

91
00:04:14,933 --> 00:04:18,000
That's embarrassing. Stop it.
They might answer you.

92
00:04:18,067 --> 00:04:20,133
The rocks might suddenly talk.

93
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:26,133
I love you so much, Celeste.

94
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,900
Okay...

95
00:04:31,967 --> 00:04:33,000
Bye. Goodnight.

96
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:08,500
Patricio!

97
00:06:10,033 --> 00:06:11,267
Mr. Ben!

98
00:06:11,333 --> 00:06:12,767
You're here.

99
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:13,967
How are you?

100
00:06:14,033 --> 00:06:15,700
I will take care of something
in the Municipal Hall.

101
00:06:15,767 --> 00:06:17,233
How are you, Mr. Ben?

102
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:18,800
This is the first time
you dropped by here.

103
00:06:18,867 --> 00:06:21,000
There's a lot of work
in the Barangay.

104
00:06:21,067 --> 00:06:24,533
I can't go around if there
are crops to plant.

105
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,700
Sebastian frequently
visits our place.

106
00:06:26,767 --> 00:06:27,967
- What?
- What?

107
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:31,700
He didn't tell me that he
frequently visits your place.

108
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:33,300
He's with his girlfriend.

109
00:06:34,767 --> 00:06:36,533
- Girlfriend?
- Girlfriend?

110
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,367
Your son has good taste.

111
00:06:38,433 --> 00:06:40,033
She's beautiful.

112
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,000
As beautiful as me?

113
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:42,633
Yes.

114
00:06:46,533 --> 00:06:48,467
Look at Sebastian.

115
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:50,167
He's keeping it
a secret from us.

116
00:06:51,267 --> 00:06:52,700
He got it from someone.

117
00:07:00,833 --> 00:07:02,800
Where? Here? Okay...

118
00:07:06,067 --> 00:07:07,000
Almost there.

119
00:07:07,067 --> 00:07:08,567
Okay.

120
00:07:11,933 --> 00:07:13,467
Surprise!

121
00:07:17,867 --> 00:07:20,000
Happy anniversary!

122
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:25,167
I forgot. Sorry.

123
00:07:25,233 --> 00:07:26,567
That's okay.

124
00:07:26,633 --> 00:07:28,800
It's the women who
are good with dates.

125
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,767
I asked Grandmother Ikay
to help me make that,

126
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:36,267
also the food that we will bring
later.

127
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:37,667
Where are we going?

128
00:07:37,733 --> 00:07:40,967
I thought of going on a picnic
in Bulusan Lake.

129
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:44,033
We can spend the night
on the hill.

130
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:47,133
Let's do stargazing all night.

131
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:52,567
Celeste has a community service
today.

132
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:53,967
I need to be there.

133
00:07:55,567 --> 00:07:58,667
But it's our anniversary.

134
00:07:58,733 --> 00:08:03,433
Can you pass that to someone
else and let them handle it?

135
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:06,733
I can try but maybe no one
is available.

136
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,233
Come on. Please?

137
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:10,500
Please.

138
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:15,400
Or don't tell me you're choosing
Celeste over me.

139
00:08:17,533 --> 00:08:18,700
Come on.

140
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:35,267
Sebastian,

141
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:37,967
you already have
a girlfriend?

142
00:08:38,033 --> 00:08:40,900
That's why it's like you're
doing a fashion show

143
00:08:40,967 --> 00:08:43,200
in front of the mirror.

144
00:08:43,267 --> 00:08:44,567
It's not that.

145
00:08:44,633 --> 00:08:46,967
It's just that my other
clothes don't suit me anymore.

146
00:08:48,167 --> 00:08:50,433
You will keep it a secret
from us?

147
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:56,233
Don't. Because your mother
and I have been there.

148
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:57,667
Who is she?

149
00:08:57,733 --> 00:08:59,833
Why don't you bring her home?

150
00:08:59,900 --> 00:09:01,500
Who told you?

151
00:09:01,567 --> 00:09:05,500
See, you still deny it.

152
00:09:05,567 --> 00:09:08,767
Mr. Ben went here.

153
00:09:08,833 --> 00:09:12,333
And he told us that you have
a girlfriend.

154
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,700
Who is she?

155
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:15,233
Is she from here?

156
00:09:15,300 --> 00:09:17,267
Do we know her?

157
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,733
You should introduce her.

158
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:25,367
Son, it would be better
if we meet her.

159
00:09:25,433 --> 00:09:26,800
You should invite her.

160
00:09:26,867 --> 00:09:28,467
Ask her to come to the house.

161
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:34,267
It's also better
if she meets us, okay?

162
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:37,300
Son, don't be shy.

163
00:09:37,367 --> 00:09:39,233
Remember whoever you love,

164
00:09:39,300 --> 00:09:41,233
your father and I
will love her too.

165
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:42,467
Of course.

166
00:09:42,533 --> 00:09:47,133
Rich or poor, beautiful
or even if she looks different

167
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:50,000
as long as you love her,
we will accept her.

168
00:09:50,067 --> 00:09:53,800
Just make sure she's not ugly,
I can't accept that.

169
00:09:53,867 --> 00:09:56,267
Wait, I'll just ask them
to get something.

170
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:59,800
Hey Paeng, come here
for a moment!

171
00:09:59,867 --> 00:10:00,800
Why Sir?

172
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:03,233
Paeng, go get some coconuts.

173
00:10:03,300 --> 00:10:05,067
Get three.

174
00:10:05,133 --> 00:10:07,300
It should be soft,
so there's a lot of juice.

175
00:10:07,367 --> 00:10:08,300
Yes, Sir.

176
00:10:08,367 --> 00:10:09,667
Sebastian will bring that.

177
00:10:09,733 --> 00:10:11,133
Okay.

178
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:22,533
Don't keep secrets especially
about your girlfriend.

179
00:10:29,167 --> 00:10:30,200
Hi, Love?

180
00:10:30,267 --> 00:10:32,600
Hello, love? Can we talk?

181
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:34,600
Yes, of course.

182
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:36,367
The person who will fetch me
is not here yet.

183
00:10:36,433 --> 00:10:39,167
I'm going to our
community service.

184
00:10:39,233 --> 00:10:41,833
Do you want to talk
about the wedding?

185
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:43,033
Something came up.

186
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:46,167
And I want you to know this.

187
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:48,633
Why? What happened?

188
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:50,433
I'm going to Thailand.
So, probably

189
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:53,000
we can't set a date yet.

190
00:10:53,067 --> 00:10:56,000
Oh, business trip?

191
00:10:56,067 --> 00:10:59,500
Yes. We're meeting with a couple
of Thai businessmen

192
00:10:59,567 --> 00:11:00,600
for a possible partnership.

193
00:11:00,667 --> 00:11:02,867
So, I'm sorry.

194
00:11:02,933 --> 00:11:04,600
This is sudden.

195
00:11:04,667 --> 00:11:06,967
No, it's okay, Sweetheart.

196
00:11:07,033 --> 00:11:09,333
I also suddenly made decisions
about our wedding

197
00:11:09,433 --> 00:11:11,600
so, don't worry about it.

198
00:11:11,667 --> 00:11:13,233
Are you traveling alone?

199
00:11:14,667 --> 00:11:17,600
That's the other thing
that I want to tell you.

200
00:11:17,667 --> 00:11:20,367
Aurelia is going with me.

201
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:27,867
Love, I know what you're
thinking

202
00:11:27,933 --> 00:11:30,933
but this is a purely
business trip.

203
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,100
I'm telling you this

204
00:11:32,167 --> 00:11:34,000
because I don't want to keep it
a secret from you.

205
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:36,167
You have to trust me on this.

206
00:11:36,233 --> 00:11:38,700
I trust you. Don't worry.

207
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:42,767
I mean, I know it's a sensitive
topic.

208
00:11:44,167 --> 00:11:45,767
Your sister might say
something about me.

209
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:50,900
But you know, you take care
and you call me.

210
00:11:50,967 --> 00:11:52,733
When do you leave?

211
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,000
I'll let you know.

212
00:11:54,067 --> 00:11:57,767
We're still booking our ticket.

213
00:11:57,833 --> 00:12:01,133
Okay. Well, thank you.

214
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,033
For what?

215
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:06,267
For being honest with me.

216
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:08,667
I appreciate that.

217
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:10,100
I love you.

218
00:12:10,167 --> 00:12:11,233
I love you, too.

219
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:13,467
I'll call you later, okay?

220
00:12:38,433 --> 00:12:39,433
Hold me.

221
00:12:44,033 --> 00:12:45,533
Miss Vangie?

222
00:13:23,533 --> 00:13:25,867
Do you remember this place?

223
00:13:25,933 --> 00:13:27,767
This exact spot?

224
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:32,067
This is where you said yes
to me, right?

225
00:13:34,467 --> 00:13:38,100
The last time we went here
was six years ago.

226
00:13:38,167 --> 00:13:40,967
So, I thought we should
celebrate here

227
00:13:41,033 --> 00:13:46,267
instead of going to the
restaurants that we usually do.

228
00:13:47,300 --> 00:13:49,233
Actually, it's better here
for a change, right?

229
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:50,833
Yes, right?

230
00:14:00,533 --> 00:14:01,633
Mikoy?

231
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:03,200
- Yeah?
- What's up?

232
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:07,533
Miss Vangie hasn't
texted me yet.

233
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:10,767
I asked her to watch over
Celeste today.

234
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,800
Could you please don't think
about Celeste now?

235
00:14:16,433 --> 00:14:18,833
This is just work,
nothing personal, okay?

236
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:22,300
Once you taste my cooking

237
00:14:22,367 --> 00:14:24,600
I'm sure you will forget
everything.

238
00:14:24,667 --> 00:14:27,333
I even asked Grandmother
Ikay to help me.

239
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,767
This is your favorite, right?

240
00:14:28,867 --> 00:14:30,367
It looks delicious.

241
00:14:30,433 --> 00:14:31,833
I'll prepare a plate for you.

242
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:42,567
Miss Vangie, where is Mikoy?

243
00:14:42,633 --> 00:14:44,667
Isn't he the one who is supposed
to pick me up?

244
00:14:47,133 --> 00:14:49,733
He texted me earlier.

245
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:51,433
He asked me to substitute
for him.

246
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:53,867
He has an emergency leave today.

247
00:14:53,933 --> 00:14:55,600
Emergency?

248
00:14:55,667 --> 00:14:57,167
Why emergency?

249
00:14:57,233 --> 00:14:59,933
Did he say something about
his grandmother or himself?

250
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,433
He didn't mention anything.

251
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:04,900
I was also in rush to leave
the house earlier.

252
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,600
I'll just make a call.

253
00:15:13,067 --> 00:15:14,267
Excuse me.

254
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,767
Hello, Celeste?

255
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:22,667
Mikoy, are you okay?

256
00:15:22,733 --> 00:15:24,233
You have an emergency?

257
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:26,767
Is there anything wrong
with you or your grandmother?

258
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:29,033
I'm just worried.

259
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,767
No. There's no emergency.

260
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:40,100
It's just that I forgot
that today is our anniversary.

261
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:42,867
So, I filed for emergency leave.

262
00:15:44,367 --> 00:15:45,800
Oh...

263
00:15:45,867 --> 00:15:47,133
okay.

264
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,700
Enjoy...

265
00:15:48,767 --> 00:15:50,767
enjoy.

266
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:01,400
Let's go, Ms. Vangie.

267
00:16:01,467 --> 00:16:11,433
Come on.

268
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:26,400
Come on.

269
00:16:53,933 --> 00:16:55,633
Let's eat.

270
00:17:06,133 --> 00:17:07,467
It's good.

271
00:17:11,233 --> 00:17:12,833
Where is that?

272
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:14,933
You know it's near.

273
00:17:15,033 --> 00:17:16,133
It's confusing.

274
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:20,100
The trees here looked the same.

275
00:17:20,167 --> 00:17:23,300
I think this is it.

276
00:17:25,267 --> 00:17:29,800
I guess this is the spot
that Mikoy is saying.

277
00:17:31,933 --> 00:17:34,333
There. Just go forward.

278
00:17:37,433 --> 00:17:38,633
Here.

279
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:40,633
This is it, okay.

280
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:45,000
Celeste, you can start planting
now.

281
00:17:45,067 --> 00:17:46,000
Okay.

282
00:17:46,067 --> 00:17:48,067
Crew, you can take footage now.

283
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,933
There.

284
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:54,233
Take a video of Ms. Celeste
planting a tree.

285
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:05,733
All of it?

286
00:18:18,733 --> 00:18:19,767
Wait.

287
00:18:30,233 --> 00:18:33,967
Hey, I said cellphone
is not allowed.

288
00:18:47,067 --> 00:18:48,400
Hello, Mikoy.

289
00:18:48,467 --> 00:18:50,733
Hello, Ms. Vangie.

290
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:52,933
How are you? How is Celeste?

291
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,200
She's okay.

292
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:55,633
We're already here in Irosin.

293
00:18:55,733 --> 00:18:58,933
Good thing there's a signal
here.

294
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,867
How is she?

295
00:19:00,933 --> 00:19:03,400
She doesn't seem to be
a troublemaker.

296
00:19:03,467 --> 00:19:05,767
Don't worry. I'll send you
pictures

297
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:07,667
so you can see what she's doing.

298
00:19:09,167 --> 00:19:10,767
Okay. I'll wait for it.

299
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:12,100
You take care there.

300
00:19:41,667 --> 00:19:43,633
Just for documentation purposes.

301
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:20,967
Mikoy?

302
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:21,967
Yeah.
What's up?

303
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:27,933
Ah...

304
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,433
someone from the Municipal
Hall sent me a text.

305
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:32,033
I'm just fixing something, pass.

306
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:33,167
Okay.

307
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:08,267
Celeste, lunch break.

308
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:10,200
Okay. I'll just finish this.

309
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:12,800
Boys?

310
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:35,133
How are you? I hope you're
enjoying Irosin.

311
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:38,400
Take care always.

312
00:21:43,267 --> 00:21:45,233
Where are we going tomorrow?

313
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:47,900
In Irosin. We'll have
a tree planting activity.

314
00:21:47,967 --> 00:21:49,967
Do you remember that place?

315
00:21:50,033 --> 00:21:52,267
We often go there
when we were teenagers.

316
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:54,100
That's where the first time
I shouted that I love you

317
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:55,600
so much.

318
00:21:57,433 --> 00:21:59,033
Mikoy is really doing
this on purpose.

319
00:21:59,100 --> 00:22:01,700
He really takes me
to places...

320
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:06,200
full of our memories.

321
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:16,767
It's beautiful here.

322
00:22:19,533 --> 00:22:22,967
I always go here
every time I'm sad.

323
00:22:23,033 --> 00:22:27,367
I'm always here
when my parents died.

324
00:22:29,667 --> 00:22:31,767
Are you sad that's why
we're here?

325
00:22:33,033 --> 00:22:34,133
No.

326
00:22:36,133 --> 00:22:37,333
I'm very happy.

327
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:44,067
And I want to replace all
the bad memories

328
00:22:44,133 --> 00:22:46,533
that I have here
with happy memories.

329
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:47,767
That's why I brought you here.

330
00:22:51,567 --> 00:22:52,933
Happy memories?

331
00:22:55,767 --> 00:22:56,933
Like this.

332
00:22:59,433 --> 00:23:01,633
I love you so much, Celeste!

333
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:02,967
Hey...

334
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:05,900
- don't be like that.
- I want to be with you forever!

335
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:09,267
I promise to this stream
and trees

336
00:23:09,333 --> 00:23:11,133
that we will never separate!

337
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:14,200
That's embarrassing. Stop it.
They might answer you back.

338
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:16,500
The rocks might suddenly talk.

339
00:23:19,967 --> 00:23:21,933
I love you so much, Celeste.

340
00:23:41,300 --> 00:23:43,433
You are a liar, Mikoy!

341
00:23:45,800 --> 00:23:48,467
You didn't fulfill
your promises.

342
00:23:53,533 --> 00:23:54,833
It was you who left me.

343
00:23:58,467 --> 00:24:00,033
I hate you...

344
00:24:02,367 --> 00:24:03,433
I hate you.

345
00:24:10,067 --> 00:24:12,567
What's this?

346
00:24:12,633 --> 00:24:13,933
Why do I still feel this?

347
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:16,833
Am I annoyed...

348
00:24:16,900 --> 00:24:17,867
that he left me?

349
00:24:17,933 --> 00:24:21,300
Do I regret that...

350
00:24:21,367 --> 00:24:23,567
we didn't end up together?

351
00:24:23,633 --> 00:24:25,367
I'm pissed off.

352
00:24:25,433 --> 00:24:26,967
I'm really pissed off.

353
00:24:58,900 --> 00:25:01,867
If you only knew how hard
it is to have parents

354
00:25:01,967 --> 00:25:04,367
who is both successful,
who are both achievers?

355
00:25:04,433 --> 00:25:07,400
They expect I can get
somewhere in my life.

356
00:25:07,467 --> 00:25:10,367
Winston, I would like to check
Tonito's schedule

357
00:25:10,433 --> 00:25:11,967
for this coming week.

358
00:25:12,033 --> 00:25:13,667
There are changes in his wedding
date with Celeste.

359
00:25:13,733 --> 00:25:16,533
They're planning to get married
this coming week in Sorsogon.

360
00:25:16,600 --> 00:25:18,267
He didn't tell me.

361
00:25:18,333 --> 00:25:20,000
Hazel, I'll be back.

362
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:22,967
Celeste?

363
00:25:24,733 --> 00:25:26,900
Celeste, I'm really sorry.

364
00:25:26,967 --> 00:25:29,267
Miss Vangie, this is Hazel.

365
00:25:29,333 --> 00:25:30,767
Is there something
I can do for you?

366
00:25:30,833 --> 00:25:32,300
Is Mikoy with you?

367
00:25:32,367 --> 00:25:35,067
He went to Celeste's house.

368
00:25:35,133 --> 00:25:39,833
I did something wrong to Basti
and I got angry.

369
00:25:39,933 --> 00:25:43,633
I want to apologize to him
but I don't know-how.

370
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:47,100
We men do something to our
sulking girlfriends.

371
00:25:47,167 --> 00:25:48,967
- What is that?
- Serenade.

372
00:25:49,033 --> 00:25:50,833
I know you went to Celeste.

373
00:25:50,900 --> 00:25:55,900
You left me for her on the day
of our anniversary, Mikoy.

374
00:25:55,967 --> 00:25:57,967
How dare you!
